 Port Elizabeth - Port Elizabeth police are investigating a case of business robbery after a local church was robbed by knife-wielding men on Tuesday. "It is alleged that on Tuesday, at 10.00, a 26-year-old complainant was in the prayer room at a local church in Govan Mbeki Street in Central, Port Elizabeth, when four suspects entered looking for the Pastor who was not in at the time," said police spokesperson, W/Off Alwin Labans. "One of the suspect’s requested to be prayed for as he had a pending court case." He said that two suspects then produced knives and robbed the complainant of his android phone. "One suspect took the complainant to the kitchen while the others ransacked the church," W/O Labans said. "They took and fled with a Lenovo laptop, Dixon music mixer, Dixon microphonce,R9,00 cash and a black android cellphone." He said that police are investigating a case of Business robbery. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 